author: Jay DiNItto

text: A game that influenced not only the fighting genre but the whole video game industry with its highly competitive nature. It's also one of the most improved sequels of all time. It's crazy to think that this game and the Champion Edition had gross revenues of 2.3+ billion dollars by 1995, which is the equivalent of 4 billion dollars now (thanks Wikipedia!). And that's just the Arcade versions. This is a game I could easily pick up now, play for hours and still have tons of fun.
